cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR

This paper is about person re-identification, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new model that combines multiple convolutional network layers, which is a machine learning technique, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses resource-constrained formulations of the problem, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper proposes a new state-of-the-art on traditional re-ID benchmarks, which could also fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
